614 - Maximum Nesting Depth of the Parentheses
Problem Statement

Given a valid parentheses string s, return the maximum nesting depth of the parentheses.

Example

Input:

s = "(1+(2*3)+((8)/4))+1"

Output:

3

Explanation:
The deepest nested parentheses are ((8)/4), which have a nesting depth of 3.

Approach
Intuition
Whenever we encounter '(', we enter a deeper level, so increase the current depth.
Whenever we encounter ')', we exit a level, so decrease the current depth.
Keep track of the maximum depth reached during traversal.
Algorithm
Initialize:
depth = 0 (current nesting level)
maxDepth = 0 (maximum depth found)
Traverse the string:
If character is '(', increment depth and update maxDepth.
If character is ')', decrement depth.
Return maxDepth.
Code
class Solution {
    public int maxDepth(String s) {
        int depth = 0;
        int maxDepth = 0;

        for (char ch : s.toCharArray()) {
            if (ch == '(') {
                depth++;
                maxDepth = Math.max(maxDepth, depth);
            } else if (ch == ')') {
                depth--;
            }
        }

        return maxDepth;
    }
}
Dry Run
Input
s = "(1+(2*3)+((8)/4))+1"
Character	Depth	MaxDepth
(	1	1
(	2	2
)	1	2
(	2	2
(	3	3
)	2	3
)	1	3
)	0	3
Output
3
Complexity Analysis
Time Complexity
O(n)
Traverse the string once.
Space Complexity
O(1)
Only a few variables are used.
Key Takeaway
Increase depth for every '('.
Decrease depth for every ')'.
Track the maximum depth encountered during traversal.
No stack is required since only the nesting depth is needed.
